[00:00.000]--- Lesson 17  Always young 青春常驻
[00:04.650]My aunt Jennifer is an actress.^我的姑姑詹妮弗是位演员，
[00:07.889]She must be at least thirty-five years old.^她至少也有35岁了。
[00:12.147]In spite of this, she often appears on the stage as a young girl.^尽管如此，她却常在舞台上扮演小姑娘。
[00:18.051]Jennifer will have to take part in a new play soon.^詹妮弗很快又要参加一个新剧的演出。
[00:22.413]This time, she will be a girl of seventeen.^这一次，她将扮演一个17岁的少女。
[00:26.697]In the play, she must appear in a bright red dress and long black stockings.^演出时她必须穿一条鲜红色的裙子和黑色的长筒袜。
[00:34.429]Last year in another play, she had to wear short socks and a bright, orange-coloured dress.^去年在演另一个剧时，她不得不穿短袜和一件鲜艳的橘红色的衣服。
[00:42.971]If anyone ever asks her how old she is, she always answers,'Darling, it must be terrible to be grown up!'^一旦有人问起她有多大年纪，她总是回答：“亲爱的，长成大人真可怕啊！”
